## Guards summary

```typescript
// AuthGuard â€” use on ALL protected routes
canActivate: [AuthGuard]

// AdminGuard â€” use on admin-only routes (/accountants)
canActivate: [AuthGuard, AdminGuard]

// PermissionGuard â€” use for fine-grained module permissions
canActivate: [AuthGuard, PermissionGuard]
data: { menuItemId: 'SALES', permissionAction: 'canView' }  // or canCreate / canEdit / canDelete
```

## Adding a new API service (pattern)

```typescript
// src/app/modules/my-module/services/my.service.ts
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class MyService {
  private readonly base = `${environment.apiUrl}/my-resource`;

  constructor(private http: HttpClient) {}

  getAll(params?: any): Observable<PageResponse<MyModel>> {
    return this.http.get<PageResponse<MyModel>>(this.base, { params });
  }

  create(dto: CreateMyDto): Observable<MyModel> {
    return this.http.post<MyModel>(this.base, dto);
  }

  update(id: number, dto: UpdateMyDto): Observable<MyModel> {
    return this.http.put<MyModel>(`${this.base}/${id}`, dto);
  }

  delete(id: number): Observable<void> {
    return this.http.delete<void>(`${this.base}/${id}`);
  }
}
```

## PageResponse model

```typescript
interface PageResponse<T> {
  content: T[];
  totalElements: number;
  totalPages: number;
  number: number;     // current page (0-based)
  size: number;       // page size
}
```

## Error handling pattern

- HTTP errors are handled globally by the interceptor (401 â†’ logout, 403 â†’ permission denied toast)
- Component-level: show `<app-erp-alert>` for caught errors
- Never swallow errors silently

